    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>sankame (hereinafter referred to as "the Developer") establishes the following privacy policy (hereinafter referred to as "this Policy") regarding the handling of users' personal information in the services (hereinafter referred to as "this Service") provided on this website and mobile applications.</p>

    <h2>Article 1 (Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>"Personal Information" refers to "personal information" as defined by the Personal Information Protection Act, and includes information about living individuals that can identify a specific person through descriptions such as name, date of birth, address, phone number, contact details, and other identifiers, as well as data related to appearance, fingerprints, voiceprints, and health insurance card numbers that can identify a specific individual from the information itself (personal identification information).</p>

    <h2>Article 2 (Collection Methods of Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>The Developer may ask users for personal information such as name, date of birth, address, phone number, email address, bank account number, credit card number, and driver's license number when registering for use. Additionally, the Developer may collect transaction records and payment information including personal information of users from the Developer's partners (including information providers, advertisers, ad distributors, etc., hereinafter referred to as "Partners").</p>

    <h2>Article 3 (Purpose of Collection and Use of Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>The purposes for which the Developer collects and uses personal information are as follows:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and operate Developer's services</li>
        <li>To respond to inquiries from users (including verifying the user's identity)</li>
        <li>To send emails about new features, updates, campaigns, and other services provided by the Developer</li>
        <li>To contact users as necessary for maintenance, important notices, etc.</li>
        <li>To identify users who violate the terms of service or attempt to use the service for fraudulent or improper purposes and to refuse their use</li>
        <li>To allow users to view, change, delete their registration information, and view their usage status</li>
        <li>To charge users for paid services</li>
        <li>To achieve the above purposes and other associated purposes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Article 4 (Changes to the Purpose of Use)</h2>
    <p>The Developer may change the purpose of use of personal information only if it is reasonably related to the purpose before the change. If the purpose of use is changed, the Developer will notify the users of the changed purpose through a method specified by the Developer or announce it on this website.</p>

    <h2>Article 5 (Provision of Personal Information to Third Parties)</h2>
    <p>Except in the cases listed below, the Developer will not provide personal information to third parties without obtaining prior consent from the user. However, this does not apply to cases permitted by the Personal Information Protection Act and other laws.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>When it is necessary to protect someone's life, body, or property, and it is difficult to obtain consent from the person</li>
        <li>When it is especially necessary to improve public health or promote the sound development of children, and it is difficult to obtain consent from the person</li>
        <li>When it is necessary to cooperate with national or local government agencies or their entrusted parties in the performance of duties prescribed by laws and regulations, and obtaining consent from the person may hinder the performance of such duties</li>
        <li>When the following matters have been announced or published in advance, and the Developer has notified the Personal Information Protection Committee:
            <ul>
                <li>Including the provision of personal information to third parties in the purpose of use</li>
                <li>Items of data provided to third parties</li>
                <li>Means or methods of providing personal information to third parties</li>
                <li>Stopping the provision of personal information to third parties upon the request of the person</li>
                <li>Methods for accepting requests from the person</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>Notwithstanding the provisions of the previous paragraph, the following cases are not considered as provision to third parties:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>When the Developer entrusts all or part of the handling of personal information within the scope necessary to achieve the purpose of use</li>
        <li>When personal information is provided due to business succession such as mergers</li>
        <li>When personal information is jointly used with specific entities, and the fact, items of personal information jointly used, scope of entities using the information, purposes of use, and the name or designation of the person responsible for managing the personal information are notified in advance to the person or made easily accessible</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Article 6 (Disclosure of Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>The Developer will disclose personal information to the person upon request without delay. However, if disclosing the information falls under any of the following cases, the Developer may choose not to disclose all or part of the information and will notify the person of the decision without delay. A fee of 1,000 yen will be charged for each disclosure request.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>When there is a risk of harming the life, body, property, or other rights and interests of the person or a third party</li>
        <li>When there is a risk of significantly hindering the proper conduct of the Developer's business</li>
        <li>When it would violate other laws</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Notwithstanding the provisions of the previous paragraph, information other than personal information such as history and characteristics information will generally not be disclosed.</p>

    <h2>Article 7 (Correction and Deletion of Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>Users can request the Developer to correct, add, or delete (hereinafter referred to as "Correction, etc.") their own personal information if it is incorrect, according to the procedures specified by the Developer. If the Developer determines that it is necessary to respond to such a request, the Developer will make the necessary corrections without delay.</p>
    <p>If the Developer makes corrections or decides not to make corrections based on the above provisions, the Developer will notify the user of the decision without delay.</p>

    <h2>Article 8 (Suspension of Use of Personal Information)</h2>
    <p>If a user requests the Developer to stop using or delete (hereinafter referred to as "Suspension of Use, etc.") their personal information because it is being handled beyond the scope of its purpose of use or was obtained through fraudulent means, the Developer will promptly conduct the necessary investigation.</p>
    <p>Based on the results of the investigation, if it is determined that it is necessary to respond to the request, the Developer will promptly suspend the use or delete the personal information.</p>
    <p>If the Developer performs suspension of use, etc., or decides not to perform suspension of use, etc., the Developer will notify the user of the decision without delay.</p>
    <p>Notwithstanding the previous two paragraphs, if the suspension of use, etc., requires substantial cost or is otherwise difficult to implement, and an alternative measure that adequately protects the userâ€™s rights and interests can be taken, the Developer will take such alternative measures.</p>

    <h2>Article 9 (Changes to the Privacy Policy)</h2>
    <p>This Policy may be changed without notifying users, except for matters stipulated by laws and regulations or other specific provisions in this Policy. Unless otherwise specified by the Developer, the revised privacy policy will become effective from the time it is posted on this website.</p>

    <h2>Article 10 (Contact for Inquiries)</h2>
    <p>For inquiries regarding this Policy, please contact:</p>
    <p>Developer: sankame<br>
    Email Address: m2ad0504@outlook.jp</p>

